26void
27dns_dbiterator_destroy(dns_dbiterator_t **iteratorp) {
28 /*
29 * Destroy '*iteratorp'.
30 */
31
32 REQUIRE(iteratorp != NULL);
33 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(*iteratorp));
34
35 (*iteratorp)->methods->destroy(iteratorp);
36
37 ENSURE(*iteratorp == NULL);
38}
39
40isc_result_t
41dns_dbiterator_first(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
42 /*
43 * Move the node cursor to the first node in the database (if any).
44 */
45
46 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
47
48 return (iterator->methods->first(iterator));
49}
50
51isc_result_t
52dns_dbiterator_last(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
53 /*
54 * Move the node cursor to the first node in the database (if any).
55 */
56
57 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
58
59 return (iterator->methods->last(iterator));
60}
61
62isc_result_t
63dns_dbiterator_seek(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, const dns_name_t *name) {
64 /*
65 * Move the node cursor to the node with name 'name'.
66 */
67
68 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
69
70 return (iterator->methods->seek(iterator, name));
71}

74dns_dbiterator_prev(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
75 /*

80

84isc_result_t

86 /*

88 */
89
90 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
91
92 return (iterator->methods->next(iterator));
93}
94
95isc_result_t
96dns_dbiterator_current(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, dns_dbnode_t **nodep,
97 dns_name_t *name)
98{
99 /*
100 * Return the current node.
101 */
102
103 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
104 REQUIRE(nodep != NULL && *nodep == NULL);
105 REQUIRE(name == NULL || dns_name_hasbuffer(name));
106
107 return (iterator->methods->current(iterator, nodep, name));
108}
109
110isc_result_t
111dns_dbiterator_pause(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator) {
112 /*
113 * Pause iteration.
114 */
115
116 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
117
118 return (iterator->methods->pause(iterator));
119}
120
121isc_result_t
122dns_dbiterator_origin(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, dns_name_t *name) {
123
124 /*
125 * Return the origin to which returned node names are relative.
126 */
127
128 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
129 REQUIRE(iterator->relative_names);
130 REQUIRE(dns_name_hasbuffer(name));
131
132 return (iterator->methods->origin(iterator, name));
133}
134
135void
136dns_dbiterator_setcleanmode(dns_dbiterator_t *iterator, bool mode) {
137 REQUIRE(DNS_DBITERATOR_VALID(iterator));
138
139 iterator->cleaning = mode;
140}
